ard A. Sirois<br>1,847\n|\n|[[R\u00e9al M\u00e9nard]]<br>1,089\n|\n|Daniel Gonzales<br>63\n|\n|Gaetan Trudel (Comm.)<br>99<br>\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Serge Joyal]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:whitesmoke;\"|[[Montreal\u2014Mercier]]\n|{{Canadian politics/party colours/Progressive Conservatives}}|\n|Carole Jacques<br>25,071\n|\n|[[C\u00e9line Hervieux-Payette]]<br>19,335\n|\n|Robert Ferland<br>4,925\n|\n|Raymond les oreilles Pollender<br>2,038\n|\n|G\u00e9rald Gigu\u00e8re<br>2,557\n|\n|Michel Destroismaisons<br>154\n|\n|\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[C\u00e9line Hervieux-Payette]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:whitesmoke;\"|[[Montreal\u2014Sainte-Marie]]\n|\n|Fran\u00e7ois Richard<br>10,668\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Jean-Claude Mal\u00e9part]]<br>13,668\n|\n|Lauraine Vaillancourt<br>3,525\n|\n|\n|\n|Andr\u00e9 Vaillancourt<br>990\n|\n|Ghislain Cot\u00e9<br>69\n|\n|\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Jean-Claude Mal\u00e9part]]<br/><small>''[[Hochelaga (electoral district)|Sainte-Marie]]''</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background:whitesmoke;\"|[[Rosemont (electoral district)|Rosemont]]\n|{{Canadian politics/party colours/Progressive Conservatives}}|\n|[[Suzanne Blais-Grenier]] <br>15,782\n|\n|Antonio Sciascia<br>14,477\n|\n|Roger J.W.D. Lamarre<br>4,054\n|\n|Francine Rose Lime Lacasse <br>1,587\n|\n|Denis Castonguay<br>1,008\n|\n|Andr\u00e9 Malboeuf<br>64\n|\n|Claude Demers (Comm.)<br>161<br>Lucien Lapointe <small>([[Social Credit Party of Canada|Social Credit]])</small><br>143<br>Dollard Desjardins (Ind.)<br>101<br>\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Claude-Andr\u00e9 Lachance]] \n|-\n| style=\"background:whitesmoke;\"|[[Saint-L\u00e9onard\u2014Anjou]]\n|\n|Agostino Cannavino <br>23,275\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Alfonso Gagliano]]<br>24,520\n|\n|Terrence Trudeau<br>7,506\n|\n|Denis La Miuf Ouellet<br>2,152<br>\n|\n|Pierre-Alain