aine Vaillancourt<br>3,525\n|\n|\n|\n|Andr\u00e9 Vaillancourt<br>990\n|\n|Ghislain Cot\u00e9<br>69\n|\n|\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Jean-Claude Mal\u00e9part]]<br/><small>''[[Hochelaga (electoral district)|Sainte-Marie]]''</small>\n|-\n| style=\"background:whitesmoke;\"|[[Rosemont (electoral district)|Rosemont]]\n|{{Canadian politics/party colours/Progressive Conservatives}}|\n|[[Suzanne Blais-Grenier]] <br>15,782\n|\n|Antonio Sciascia<br>14,477\n|\n|Roger J.W.D. Lamarre<br>4,054\n|\n|Francine Rose Lime Lacasse <br>1,587\n|\n|Denis Castonguay<br>1,008\n|\n|Andr\u00e9 Malboeuf<br>64\n|\n|Claude Demers (Comm.)<br>161<br>Lucien Lapointe <small>([[Social Credit Party of Canada|Social Credit]])</small><br>143<br>Dollard Desjardins (Ind.)<br>101<br>\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Claude-Andr\u00e9 Lachance]] \n|-\n| style=\"background:whitesmoke;\"|[[Saint-L\u00e9onard\u2014Anjou]]\n|\n|Agostino Cannavino <br>23,275\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Alfonso Gagliano]]<br>24,520\n|\n|Terrence Trudeau<br>7,506\n|\n|Denis La Miuf Ouellet<br>2,152<br>\n|\n|Pierre-Alain Cotnoir<br>1,634\n|\n|Jean Vigneault<br>145\n|\n|\n|{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|background}}|\n|[[Monique B\u00e9gin]] \n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Canada macroriding}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Canadian Federal Election Results In Eastern Montreal}}\n[[Category:Canadian federal election results in Quebec|Montreal, E]]\n[[Category:Politics of Montreal]]\n", "name_user": "Amrcmln", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eResults by riding", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canadian_federal_election_results_in_Eastern_Montreal"}
{"title_page": "Josh X", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{upe|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| birth_name       = Josh Xantus\n| alias            = Josh X\n| birth_place      = [[Brooklyn, NY]]\n| genre            = [[Trap music|Trap]], [[R&B]]\n| occupation       = Singer, songwriter, producer\n| instrument       = Piano\n| years_active     = 2009\u2013present\n| label            = [[Epic Records]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Cardi B]]\n| website          = https://joshxantusmusic.com\n}}\n\n'''Josh Xantus''', known professionally as '''Josh X''', is a [[Haitian Americans|Haitian-American]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://onewestmagazine.com/magazine/2017/03/29/josh-x-stevie-wonders-latest-protege-releases-feel-good-song-promise/|title=JOSH X, Stevie Wonder's Latest Protege' Releases the Feel Good Song \"PROMISE\" \u2013 One West Magazine|date=March 29, 2017|work=One West Magazine|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> singer, songwriter, and record producer best known for ''Heaven on My Mind''.\n\n== Early life and education ==\nXantus was born in [[Brooklyn|Brooklyn, NY]] and raised by a single mother in [[Queens|Queens, NY]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kreyolicious.com/josh-x/29497|title=Josh X On Collaborating With Cardi B and On His Career As a Singer-Songwriter |date=January 29, 2018|work=Kreyolicious.com|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehypemagazine.com/2017/02/josh-x-tops-billboard-charts-with-cardi-b/|title=Josh X Tops Billboard Charts with Cardi B|work=The Hype Magazine|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> He began playing classical piano at age six and composed his first song at age 13.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.essence.com/celebrity/new-next-meet-rising-star-josh-xantus/|title=New & Next: Meet Rising Star Josh Xantus |work=Essence|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> He attended the summer program at the [[Juilliard School]] and after receiving a full college scholarship,<ref name=\":0\" /> graduated from [[Five Towns College]] in [[Long Island|Long Island, NY]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://joshxantusmusic.com/bio/|title=Bio|date=December 10, 2012|work=Josh X Official Website|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe cites [[Brian McKnight]] as his favorite singer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://singersroom.com/content/2017-01-03/exclusive-josh-x-talks-new-single-heaven-on-my-mind-his-ideal-woman-working-with-cardi-b-remaining-humble-and-more/|title=[EXCLUSIVE] Josh X Talks New Single 'Heaven on My Mind,' His Ideal Woman, Working With Cardi B, Remaining Humble, and More |date=January 3, 2017|work=Singersroom.com|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nWhile in Los Angeles in 2009, Xantus performed his single \"First Time\" for [[Stevie Wonder]], who praised his work, telling him to \"continue to carry out the legacy of being a musician that represents real music.\"<ref>{{Citation|last=JOSH X|title=Josh X-an-tus Performing \"First Time\" For Stevie Wonder|date=June 17, 2009|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ccxt_yeu6Bw|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=JOSH X|title=Stevie Wonder's Words Of Wisdom For Josh X-an-tus|date=July 27, 2009|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dXed-mq3hH0|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vibe.com/2016/11/cardi-b-josh-x-heaven-on-my-mind/|title=Josh X And Cardi B Star In 'Heaven on My Mind' Visual|date=November 16, 2016|work=Vibe|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn 2015, he co-wrote the track \"Ready to Go\" with [[Swizz Beatz]] for [[Pepsi]] and [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox's]] ''[[Empire (FOX TV series)|Empire]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thesource.com/2017/03/01/on-the-rise-josh-x-releases-mixtape-amour-aka-the-prelude-i-am-josh-x/|title=On The Rise: Josh X Releases Mixtape, \"AMOUR aka THE PRELUDE \u2013 I AM JOSH X\" {{!}} The Source|date=March 1, 2017|work=The Source|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> and released his debut single \"All for Love\" featuring [[Jadakiss]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://youknowigotsoul.com/new-music-josh-xantus-love-featuring-jadakiss|title=New Music: Josh Xantus \"All for Love\" featuring JadaKiss |date=June 26, 2014|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> That same year, he began writing and producing for rapper [[Cardi B]], and collaborated on the tracks \"Selfish\", \"Island Girls\", and \"Heaven on My Mind\" the following year.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bet.com/music/2016/12/09/josh-x-makes-a-strong-first-impression-with-the-help-of-cardi-b.html|title=Josh X Makes a Strong First Impression With the Help of Cardi B|work=BET.com|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7974045/cardi-b-best-songs-list-stream|title=9 Songs That Prove Cardi B's Rap Skills|work=Billboard|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/neev9q/listen-to-hoodcelebrityys-cardi-b-approved-new-mixtape-trap-reggae|title=Listen to HoodCelebrityy's Cardi B-Approved New Mixtape, \u2018Trap Vs. Reggae\u2019|date=August 11, 2017|work=Noisey|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> \"Heaven on My Mind\" ranked at No. 22 on the [[Billboard charts|Billboard]] [[Adult R&B Songs]] charts in January 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/cardi-b/chart-history/hot-adult-r-and-b-airplay/song/991372|title=Cardi B Heaven on My Mind Chart History|work=Billboard|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> He continued working with [[Cardi B]] for three years. In 2018, Xantus signed with record label [[Epic Records]] and released the single \"All On Me\" featuring [[Rick Ross]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/brandfeatures/venture-capital/article?id=47468|title=Josh X delivers another hit 'All On Me' Featuring Rick Ross following Billboard debut record with Cardi B \u2013 Reuters|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/rick-ross-and-josh-x-team-up-for-miami-ballad-all-on-me-new-song.1978089.html|title=Rick Ross & Josh X Team Up For Miami Ballad \"All On Me\"|work=HotNewHipHop|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> The music video received over 3.7&nbsp;million views on YouTube.<ref>{{Citation|last=JOSHXVEVO|title=Josh X \u2013 All On Me ft. Rick Ross|date=August 9, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8GU3Op24ZDA|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe has also collaborated with [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]], [[Lil Wayne]], and [[Jim Jones (rapper)|Jim Jones]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Label\n!Other Artist(s)\n!Notes\n|-\n|2015\n|''All For Love''\n|Independent\n|[[Jadakiss]]\n|(as Josh Xantus)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2016\n|''Bussin' Plays''\n|Majic City Network\n|Monee Baggz\n|\n|-\n|''Island Girls''\n|[[Epic Records|KSR Group]]\n|[[Cardi B]], Young Chow\n|\n|-\n|''Heaven on My Mind''\n|[[Epic Records|KSR Group]]\n|[[Cardi B]]\n|\n|-\n|''Selfish''\n|[[Epic Records|KSR Group]]\n|[[Cardi B]]\n|Featured artist\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n|''Amour''\n|[[Epic Records|KSR Group]]\n|Dro\n|EP\n|-\n|''First Time''\n|Taken Over Sound\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n|''All On Me''\n|[[Epic Records]]\n|[[Rick Ross]]\n|\n|-\n|''Love Lost''\n|Female Shotta Records\n|[[HoodCelebrityy]]\n|\n|}\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/josh-x/904818803#see-all/recent-albums|title=Josh X on Apple Music|website=Apple Music|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/artist/2h2eheYRqB6maoKoP76zsc|title=Josh X|website=Spotify|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/joshxantus|title=Josh Xantus|website=SoundCloud|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=CARDI B \u2013 SELFISH ft. @JoshXantus (Produced by @JoshXantus)|url=https://soundcloud.com/iamcardib/6-cardi-b-selfish|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{official|url=https://joshxantusmusic.com}}\n* [https://soundcloud.com/joshxantus Josh X on SoundCloud]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Record producers from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Rappers from New York City]]\n[[Category:21st-century American rappers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{upe|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = \n| caption          = \n| birth_name       = Josh Xantus\n| alias            = Josh X\n| birth_place      = [[Brooklyn, NY]]\n| genre            = [[Trap music|Trap]], [[R&B]]\n| occupation       = Singer, songwriter, producer\n| instrument       = Piano\n| years_active     = 2009\u2013present\n| label            = [[Epic Records]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Cardi B]]\n| website          = https://joshxantusmusic.com\n}}\n\n'''Josh Xantus''', known professionally as '''Josh X''', is a [[Haitian Americans|Haitian-American]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://onewestmagazine.com/magazine/2017/03/29/josh-x-stevie-wonders-latest-protege-releases-feel-good-song-promise/|title=JOSH X, Stevie Wonder's Latest Protege' Releases the Feel Good Song \"PROMISE\" \u2013 One West Magazine|date=March 29, 2017|work=One West Magazine|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> singer, songwriter, and record producer best known for ''Heaven on My Mind''.\n\n== Early life and education ==\nXantus was born in [[Brooklyn|Brooklyn, NY]] and raised by a single mother in [[Queens|Queens, NY]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kreyolicious.com/josh-x/29497|title=Josh X On Collaborating With Cardi B and On His Career As a Singer-Songwriter |date=January 29, 2018|work=Kreyolicious.com|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehypemagazine.com/2017/02/josh-x-tops-billboard-charts-with-cardi-b/|title=Josh X Tops Billboard Charts with Cardi B|work=The Hype Magazine|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> He began playing classical piano at age six and composed his first song at age 13.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.essence.com/celebrity/new-next-meet-rising-star-josh-xantus/|title=New & Next: Meet Rising Star Josh Xantus |work=Essence|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> He attended the summer program at the [[Juilliard School]] and after receiving a full college scholarship,<ref name=\":0\" /> graduated from [[Five Towns College]] in [[Long Island|Long Island, NY]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://joshxantusmusic.com/bio/|title=Bio|date=December 10, 2012|work=Josh X Official Website|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe cites [[Brian McKnight]] as his favorite singer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://singersroom.com/content/2017-01-03/exclusive-josh-x-talks-new-single-heaven-on-my-mind-his-ideal-woman-working-with-cardi-b-remaining-humble-and-more/|title=[EXCLUSIVE] Josh X Talks New Single 'Heaven on My Mind,' His Ideal Woman, Working With Cardi B, Remaining Humble, and More |date=January 3, 2017|work=Singersroom.com|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nWhile in Los Angeles in 2009, Xantus performed his single \"First Time\" for [[Stevie Wonder]], who praised his work, telling him to \"continue to carry out the legacy of being a musician that represents real music.\"<ref>{{Citation|last=JOSH X|title=Josh X-an-tus Performing \"First Time\" For Stevie Wonder|date=June 17, 2009|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ccxt_yeu6Bw|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=JOSH X|title=Stevie Wonder's Words Of Wisdom For Josh X-an-tus|date=July 27, 2009|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dXed-mq3hH0|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=h