<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/cardi-b/chart-history/hot-adult-r-and-b-airplay/song/991372|title=Cardi B Heaven on My Mind Chart History|work=Billboard|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> He continued working with [[Cardi B]] for three years. In 2018, Xantus signed with record label [[Epic Records]] and released the single \"All On Me\" featuring [[Rick Ross]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/brandfeatures/venture-capital/article?id=47468|title=Josh X delivers another hit 'All On Me' Featuring Rick Ross following Billboard debut record with Cardi B \u2013 Reuters|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/rick-ross-and-josh-x-team-up-for-miami-ballad-all-on-me-new-song.1978089.html|title=Rick Ross & Josh X Team Up For Miami Ballad \"All On Me\"|work=HotNewHipHop|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> The music video received over 3.7&nbsp;million views on YouTube.<ref>{{Citation|last=JOSHXVEVO|title=Josh X \u2013 All On Me ft. Rick Ross|date=August 9, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8GU3Op24ZDA|access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe has also collaborated with [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]], [[Lil Wayne]], and [[Jim Jones (rapper)|Jim Jones]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Label\n!Other Artist(s)\n!Notes\n|-\n|2015\n|''All For Love''\n|Independent\n|[[Jadakiss]]\n|(as Josh Xantus)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2016\n|''Bussin' Plays''\n|Majic City Network\n|Monee Baggz\n|\n|-\n|''Island Girls''\n|[[Epic Records|KSR Group]]\n|[[Cardi B]], Young Chow\n|\n|-\n|''Heaven on My Mind''\n|[[Epic Records|KSR Group]]\n|[[Cardi B]]\n|\n|-\n|''Selfish''\n|[[Epic Records|KSR Group]]\n|[[Cardi B]]\n|Featured artist\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n|''Amour''\n|[[Epic Records|KSR Group]]\n|Dro\n|EP\n|-\n|''First Time''\n|Taken Over Sound\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n|''All On Me''\n|[[Epic Records]]\n|[[Rick Ross]]\n|\n|-\n|''Love Lost''\n|Female Shotta Reco